---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | latepaycalc.com';
const description = 'How latepaycalc.com handles your data: what we collect, the case-review form, cookies, advertising, and your rights under GDPR, CCPA, and COPPA.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last Updated: July 2026.</em></p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy describes how latepaycalc.com ("we," "us," or "our"), operated by The Click Lab Agency LLC, collects, uses, and shares information when you visit our website at latepaycalc.com. We are committed to handling your data transparently &mdash; including being specific about what happens if you use the "Late Payment / Final Paycheck" case-review form, since that is the one part of this site that shares your information with attorneys. By using this site, you agree to the practices described below.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p><strong>Information from the calculator.</strong> Any data entered into the late-pay penalty calculator &mdash; your hourly rate or salary, state of employment, dates of separation and final-paycheck delivery, regular pay schedule, and other contextual details &mdash; runs entirely in your browser. The information you enter to estimate late-pay penalties is not transmitted to our servers, is not stored server-side, and is not logged.</p>
  <p><strong>Information from the case-review form.</strong> If you fill out and submit the "Late Payment / Final Paycheck" case-review form on this site, we collect the information you enter &mdash; typically your name, phone number, email address, and details about your situation &mdash; along with a timestamp and record of the consent language you agreed to. This is a separate, optional step from using the calculator; see Section 5 for what happens to this information.</p>
  <p><strong>Information you send us directly.</strong> If you contact us via email, we receive the information you choose to send (your name, email address, and message content).</p>
  <p><strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> Like most websites, we and our service providers automatically collect limited technical information when you visit, including IP address, browser type and version, device type, operating system, referring URL, pages visited, time spent on pages, and approximate geographic location derived from IP. This is used for analytics, performance, and security purposes.</p>
  <p><strong>Cookies and similar technologies.</strong> We use cookies and similar tracking technologies. See Section 4 below for details.</p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>To operate, maintain, and improve the site and our late-pay calculator</li>
    <li>To analyze usage trends and understand which guides and tools are most useful</li>
    <li>To respond to contact inquiries and corrections</li>
    <li>To serve relevant advertising through Google AdSense</li>
    <li>If you submit the case-review form, to share your information with attorneys or their agents so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it (see Section 5)</li>
    <li>To detect and prevent fraud, abuse, or violations of our Terms of Service</li>
    <li>To comply with applicable legal obligations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Advertising and Google AdSense</h2>
  <p>We use Google AdSense, a third-party advertising service provided by Google LLC, to display advertisements on this website. Google uses cookies &mdash; including the DoubleClick DART cookie &mdash; to serve ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visits to our site and other sites on the internet.</p>
  <p>Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a user's prior visits to this website or other websites.</p>
  <p>You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting Google's Ads Settings at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.google.com/settings/ads</a>. You may also opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.aboutads.info/choices</a> (for U.S. residents) or <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.youronlinechoices.eu</a> (for EU residents).</p>
  <p>Google's privacy policy is available at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>.</p>

  <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
  <p>A cookie is a small text file stored on your device by your browser. We use three categories of cookies:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> required for basic site functionality, such as remembering your cookie consent preferences.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> (Google Analytics, where installed) used to understand aggregate site usage.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising cookies</strong> (via Google AdSense and its partners) used to serve relevant ads and to measure ad performance.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings, including blocking or deleting them, although disabling cookies may affect site functionality. By continuing to use this site, you consent to our use of cookies as described in this policy. EU/UK/EEA users will be shown a cookie consent banner where required by law.</p>

  <h2>5. The Case-Review Form &mdash; Shared With Attorneys</h2>
  <p>The homepage includes a "Late Payment / Final Paycheck" case-review form. Submitting it is always optional; you can use the calculator and read every guide on this site without ever seeing or completing it. <strong>This form is the only place on the site where personal information is shared outside The Click Lab Agency LLC's own operations (aside from the service providers in Section 6).</strong></p>
  <p><strong>If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it.</strong> The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates latepaycalc.com, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals. This arrangement is disclosed on the form itself at the point of submission.</p>
  <p>By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email &mdash; including by automated dialing technology &mdash; by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it by not submitting the form.</p>
  <p><strong>The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form.</strong> If you've already submitted it and want to stop being contacted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[OPT-OUT]</code>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>. We will notify the attorney or agent your information was shared with and remove you from further outreach on our end.</p>

  <h2>6. Sharing Your Information With Service Providers</h2>
  <p>Beyond the attorneys or their agents described in Section 5, we do not sell personal information. We share limited information only with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Service providers</strong> (hosting, analytics, ad networks) who process data on our behalf under confidentiality obligations. Current service providers include Google AdSense, Google Analytics, Cloudflare (DNS and edge delivery), and Hostinger (registrar).</li>
    <li><strong>Legal authorities</strong> when required by law, subpoena, or court order.</li>
    <li><strong>Successors</strong> in the event of a business transfer, merger, or acquisition.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Your Rights Under GDPR (EU/UK/EEA Users)</h2>
  <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, you have the following rights under the General Data Protection Regulation: the right to access, correct, erase ("right to be forgotten"), restrict processing of, port, and object to processing of your personal data. You also have the right to withdraw consent at any time and to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</p>
  <p>Our lawful bases for processing are (a) your consent &mdash; for advertising and analytics cookies, and for case-review form submissions, given at the point of submission and withdrawable at any time by emailing us &mdash; and (b) our legitimate interest in operating and securing the site. To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

  <h2>8. Your Rights Under CCPA (California Residents)</h2>
  <p>If you are a California resident, you have the following rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The right to know what personal information we collect and how it is used.</li>
    <li>The right to request deletion of personal information.</li>
    <li>The right to opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information.</li>
    <li>The right to non-discrimination for exercising your privacy rights.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell personal information for money. However, two things may be considered a "sale" or "sharing" under CCPA/CPRA: the use of advertising cookies, and sharing your case-review form submission with attorneys in exchange for compensation (Section 5). To opt out of either, use your browser's Global Privacy Control signal, adjust cookie settings, not submit the case-review form, or email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line "CCPA Opt-Out Request." We will respond within 45 days. We do not sell or share data collected through anonymous site browsing alone.</p>

  <h2>9. Children's Privacy (COPPA)</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed at children under the age of 13, and the case-review form is not intended for use by anyone under 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected such information, we will delete it promptly. Parents or guardians who believe their child has submitted information should contact <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>

  <h2>10. Data Security</h2>
  <p>We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect information, including HTTPS for all traffic and access controls on internal systems. However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

  <h2>11. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>We retain contact-form and case-review form submissions for no longer than 24 months unless a longer period is required by law. Server access logs are retained for up to 90 days. Aggregated analytics data may be retained for up to 26 months in accordance with Google Analytics defaults.</p>

  <h2>12. International Data Transfers</h2>
  <p>The site is hosted on servers that may be located outside your country of residence. By using this site, you consent to the transfer of your information to such jurisdictions. We rely on Standard Contractual Clauses or equivalent safeguards for transfers of EU/UK personal data to jurisdictions without an adequacy decision.</p>

  <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes &mdash; especially anything affecting the case-review form &mdash; will be announced by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page and, when significant, by displaying a banner on the homepage for at least 30 days. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

  <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>For any privacy-related questions, requests, or complaints, contact:</p>
  <p>The Click Lab Agency LLC<br />Email: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a></p>
</BaseLayout>
